Dear Parent/Guardian,

School safety and security is our top priority. To further enhance the safety of our students and staff, the Board of Ed will be conducting a Voter Referendum on Tuesday, Oct. 2. Polls will be open from 2 - 8 PM.

The remaining information sessions will be held as follows:

Sept. 13 @ 7:30 PM, NE Media Center (FSA Meeting)
Sept. 20 @ 6:15 PM, CGHS Auditorium (Open House)
Sept. 20 @ 7:30 PM, SE Media Center (FSA Meeting)
Sept. 27 @ 6:30 PM, MMS Auditorium (Open House)

Additional information can be found in the Friday Folder.

post_text:
Did you know that April is Autism Awareness Month? The U.S. recognizes April as a special opportunity to educate the public about autism and issues within the autism community. Autism is a general term that describes a complex brain-based condition that can affect a person's ability to communicate, form social relationships and is often accompanied by behavioral challenges.

On Wednesday, April 18th, the Cedar Grove Public Library will be hosting a Community Autism Awareness Event at 7 PM. The CGHS Chorus will perform and the award-winning documentary "Swim Team" will be shown.

Thank you in advance for your support!

post_text:
Hello CG Community,

Please join us this Thursday, March 15 from 4-8 PM in the CGHS Cafeteria for the Cedar Grove Education Foundation's inaugural "Taste of the Arts in CG" event!

This wonderful affair will feature a community art show highlighting our ever-so-talented local professionals, as well as student artists exhibiting paintings, drawings, photography, sculpture, and pottery. Admission includes coffee, tea, dessert and entertainment by the CGHS Choir and Orchestra: $5.00 per adult, $3.00 per senior/student.

This big event will also include a silent auction for any patrons interested in obtaining some of our artists' productions!

Please stop by CGHS this Thursday to support your local education foundation. Hope to see you there!

post_text:
A big THANK YOU to the SE and NE FSAs for supporting today's assembly entitled Bully-Proof Your School - The Magic of Character.

By using magic, humor, and audience participation, the assembly helped motivate students to develop positive character traits and provided concrete tools to deal with bullies who won't go away!

The major themes of the assembly are: Respect, Responsibility, and Caring. Jim Vagias taught the children three steps to follow when faced with a bully: No, Go, & Tell.

This engaging show was brought to CG to complement our anti-bullying programming.

post_text:
After School Child Care Available For Pre-K Students

With the help of the YMCA of Montclair, we are pleased to confirm that after care through the Y will now be available to Pre-K students at both South End and North End for the upcoming school year. If you are interested in signing up for this program with the YMCA, you can visit http://ycdn.montclairymca.org/files/SCHOOL_AGE_CHILD_CARE_GUIDE.pdf for more information.

The program begins at school dismissal and children are to be picked up by 6:30 p.m. On half days the program will begin at dismissal time.

For all children who need to start the program on the first day of school ‚Äî registration must be completed on or before Thursday, August 24.

If you have any questions about the program, contact Lisa Aulisi, Senior Program Director, School Age Child Care at the YMCA of Montclair at laulisi@montclairymca.org or 973-415-6134.
